 problems is the **Root Mean Square Error (RMSE)**. This is similar to the obejective function of an OLS regression.\n","\n","Even though the RMSE is generally the preferred performance measure for regression tasks, in some contexts you may prefer to use another function. For example, suppose that there are many outlier districts. In that case, you may consider using the **mean absolute error (MAE)**"],"metadata":{"id":"JE6eHwLaoVbZ"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 2 Get the data\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"TyhZFeEwlfRT"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["In typical environments your data would be available in a relational database and spread acros multiple tables/documents/files. To access it, you would first need to get your credentials and access authorizations and familiarize yourself with the data schema. In this project, however, things are much simpler: uplad the csv file and load the data using pandas."],"metadata":{"id":"k6rAkgHfqBV_"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","housing = pd.read_csv(\"/content/housing.csv\")"],"metadata":{"id":"YVC6vChWv6Yh","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1771279237158,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":26,"user":{"displayName":"Ben Xue","userId":"08600776733826581408"}}},"execution_count":39,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Let’s have an overview of the entire dataset."],"metadata":{"id":"wotpOp6GrCzY"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["housing.head()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":206},"id":"DMHbntAHrBP4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1771279237197,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":3,"user":{"displayName":"Ben Xue","userId":"08600776733826581408"}},"outputId":"b7f27abd-1d2c-42bd-8031-8eb6404c2c09"},"execution_count":40,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["   longitude  latitude  housing_median_age  total_rooms  total_bedrooms  \\\n","0    -122.23     37.88                41.0        880.0           129.0   \n","1    